EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Army to permanently discontinue the practice of shooting and experimenting on living pigs for the purpose of training soldiers how to treat critical gunshot wounds.
EventItemMatterName: United States Army to permanently discontinue the practice of shooting and experimenting on living pigs for the purpose of training soldiers how to treat critical gunshot wounds.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to support and pass legislation that would make it unlawful to force feed a bird, by hand or machine, for the purpose of the fatty enlargement of the bird's liver.
EventItemMatterName: Make it unlawful to force feed a bird, by hand or machine, for the purpose of the fatty enlargement of the bird's liver.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign H.R.1397/S.811, the Employment Non-Discrimination Act, which would prohibit employment discrimination on the basis of actual or perceived sexual orientation and gender identity.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibit employment discrimination on the basis of actual or perceived sexual orientation and gender identity. (HR 1397/S.811)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to amend the New York State Public Service Law in order to prevent the over-saturation of communities with electric generating facilities that rely on fossil fuels.
EventItemMatterName: Prevent the over-saturation of communities with electric generating facilities that rely on fossil fuels.
